A conversion of the Source Filmmaker/Team Fortress 2 Devtest map for CS:S. Basically just an earlier version of 2Fort without the TF2 assets.

Includes an (autogenerated) nav mesh, a couple paths closed off because the bots kept getting themselves stuck, and some water beneath the bridge, because there wasn't any there at first for some reason.

Other than that, I didn't change anything. There's no bomb site or hostages, it's just a Deathmatch-like map.

Revamped and reworked version of the popular zm_nighthunt map released in 2016. Better visuals, well-thought out spaces, more hiding spots and new secrets.

This map was started shortly after the release of bhop_goldsrc as I had overwhelming requests to make a longer version of the bonus. In total, I managed to fit 10 Half-Life BSPs into one map. Brushsides are at 99.2% capacity with optimization already, otherwise I would've included more maps. Note that I modified all of the stages to improve them for auto-bhop, but I made sure they were possible on scroll as well. I've put together a playlist of some previous versions too. Many Half-Life BSPs were tested for map flow, but were cut. View it here.

Enjoy!

_sText:
de_metrobudapest is a port of the de_metrobudapest map from the Counter-Strike: Global Offensive game.

On 12-SEP-2010 the first Metro Budapest map has been released for CS:S. This small, renovated, anniversary version is here to commemorate that event while also looking back at r.man's past 15 years of involvement with Source.

New features:

Fitted for Demolition gameplay with two bomb sites (Classic and Deathmatch are also available), new cover layout, mid section and trains are running on both sides. The first arrivals are random between 5-17 sec, than 20 second each until the actual round ends. For better tracking of these intervals several counters has been placed for each directions. Trains will sound their horns if a player is within dangerous range.
40-45 seconds map. My first map made from scratches :) Enjoy!

The SEAL Team 6 Mission is simple, take over the Terrorists base, they landed at the helipad but terrorists were alerted, leading to chaos, meanwhile the terrorist has to abort from defending the base, they were contacted to instead blow to the base up, and here we are.

Made In 3 & A Half Days

=Errors=
-Bots work 60% Fine, they always hide in crates and usually gets stuck on this wooden plank which is secretly a door, there's a handle kind of thing next to it however bots don't use the handle.
-Shadows on the helicopter is dark, really dark, you can comment if you want it to be gone.
-For some reason it only spawns 4 bots (+1 = you) which means its a 5v5... not a 10v10, you can add bots via devconsole if you want 10v10.
